# JackSparrow Project Documentation Context

**Canonical documentation** lives only in the repository root index and fifteen numbered guides:

- [DOCUMENTATION.md](../../DOCUMENTATION.md) — index
- [docs/01-architecture.md](../../docs/01-architecture.md) through [docs/15-audit-report.md](../../docs/15-audit-report.md)

**To load documentation context in Cursor:**

- Use `@docs/03-ml-models.md` (or any `0N-*.md`) for the live files under `docs/`.
- The `.cursor/context/docs/` folder may be a **stale mirror**; prefer `@docs/` paths unless you have refreshed the mirror.

**Important topics by doc:**

| Doc | Use for |
|-----|---------|
| 01 | Architecture, startup, communication |
| 02 | MCP protocols |
| 03 | Models, `MODEL_DIR`, bundles, training notebook |
| 04–05 | Features, reasoning, HOLD/MTF |
| 06–07 | Backend API, WebSocket, frontend |
| 08–09 | Layout, UI/UX |
| 10–11 | Deploy, Docker, build, tests |
| 12–13 | Logging, debugging |
| 14–15 | Rules, audit / remediation |

**Note:** This rule does not auto-load documentation. Load files explicitly when needed.
